<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 6:43AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...HEAVY SNOW OCCURRING...
At 640 AM MDT, heavy snow was occurring over Great Falls and
surrounding areas of Cascade County. Snow will impact travel
through the morning commute, before changing back to rain later
this morning.
HAZARD...Heavy snow with snow rates up to 2 inches per hour.
Visibility reduced to one-quarter mile or less at times.
IMPACT...Travel will be very difficult due to ice and slush,
along with hydroplaning hazard and low visibility in splash back
and spray.</description>
